The AmaZulu royal family says the coronation of the new king, Misuzulu KaZwelithini will go ahead. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The AmaZulu royal family says the coronation of the new king, Misuzulu KaZwelithini will go ahead. This comes after the Pietermaritzburg High Court matter adjourned an urgent application brought by some senior members of the royal family. READ: AmaZulu king to begin duties They want to interdict the execution of the late King's will. The will appointed Queen Mantfombi Dlamini-Zulu as a Regent of the AmaZulu nation. Before her untimely passing, the Queen Regent nominated her son Misuzulu KaZwelithini as the king's successor.